text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Hawaii was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Former Vice President Joe Biden and his running mate U.S. SenatorKamala Harrishad won 4 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:21st century in Hawaii
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Hawaii
